      <akn:section eId="sec_38_826_01">
        <akn:num>38-826.01</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Local wellness policies.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_38-826_01_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>As required by federal law, each local educational agency shall collaborate with parents, students, food service providers, and community organizations to develop, adopt, and update a comprehensive local wellness policy. Local wellness policies shall be revised at least once every 3 years.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_38-826_01_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Local wellness policies shall include:</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_38-826_01_c">
      <akn:num>(c)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Public schools and public charter schools shall promote their local wellness policy to faculty, staff, parents, and students. A copy shall be:</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_38-826_01_d">
      <akn:num>(d)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>The Office of the State Superintendent of Education shall review each local wellness policy to ensure that it complies with federal requirements and shall examine whether schools comply with their policies.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
